	<!-- ── Usage descriptions ────────────────────────────────────────────
	     The app never captures photos/video or motion data; it only reads hardware
	     capability metadata. The strings still ship because the frameworks are linked
	     (AVFoundation camera enumeration, CoreMotion availability checks) and honest
	     descriptions preempt ITMS-90683 upload rejections. -->
	<key>NSCameraUsageDescription</key>
	<string>DeviceDNA reads camera hardware specifications (lens count, flash, stabilization) for the diagnostics report. It never captures photos or video.</string>
	<key>NSMotionUsageDescription</key>
	<string>DeviceDNA checks which motion sensors (accelerometer, gyroscope, barometer, pedometer) are present for the diagnostics report. It never records motion data.</string>
	<key>NSLocationWhenInUseUsageDescription</key>
	<string>DeviceDNA uses your approximate location permission only when iOS requires it to display the name of the currently connected Wi-Fi network. Location coordinates are never collected.</string>

	<!-- ── Export compliance: HTTPS only (exempt) — skips the encryption questionnaire. -->
	<key>ITSAppUsesNonExemptEncryption</key>
	<false/>

	<!-- ── Sync backend base URL, injected from Config.xcconfig (SYNC_BASE_URL) ─── -->
